fiery /ˈfaɪərɪ/

(fieriest) 

1. ADJ If you describe something as fiery , you mean that it is burning strongly or contains fire. 雄雄燃烧的 [文学性] 

例： A helicopter crashed in a fiery explosion in Vallejo. 一架直升机在瓦列霍起火爆炸后坠毁了。 

2. ADJ You can use fiery for emphasis when you are referring to bright colours such as red or orange. 火一般的 (颜色) [文学性] 

例： The sky turned from fiery orange to lemon yellow. 天空由火红色变成了柠檬黄。

